
{ Rulesets, selectors, declarations, properties and property values

  { Declaration

    A *declaration* consists of a ‚Üí development/web/CSS/properties[property (name)] and the assigned *property value*.

    The property value follows the property name and is separated by a colon from it:
code {
‚Üí development/web/CSS/properties/position: absolute
code }

    Multiple declarations are separated by a semicolon (`;`) from each other:
code {
‚Üí development/web/CSS/properties/position: absolute; ‚Üí development/web/CSS/properties/font-family: monospace; ‚Ä¶
